The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 26 October is 758,145 (1,346.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 21 October, there were 117,863 new confirmed cases (209.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 14 October, there were 96,024 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 23% (21,839 extra cases).
